description: 1542 Mon Ark Jon Boat. I have the title, boat is from the 1970s, however it's in perfect fishing shape. Pushes the boat surprisingly well, solo, with the weight trimmed, it darn near get's on plane. 45lb thrust bow mount foot control minn kota trolling motor new battery group 29 interstate older fish finder that works boat is wired with little LED lights that requires a small 12v battery, (I dropped mine overboard and never bought another) both bench seats are hollowed out for storage, the tops are on hinges. Lastly, there is a set of oars included. The only bad about the boat is that it has gray paint on it that is flaked off on the inside of the boat. It does not affect the ability of the operator to put fish in the boat! but it could use a good rattle can job. If you're interested, I'm asking 1900 obo. It's a total package for fishing, you just need to throw in your tackle and cooler and go. I will even include the minn kota battery charger I have for the deep cycle battery.  If you're interested, text me and I'll send over a picture. I don't have many, and the boat is in a storage unit now. Reason for selling is just that.
